I am currently a level 20 monk, and while grouped with a 26 cleric and a 24? shaman I was trying to carefully pull singles out of the sarnak fort in loio. Got one pair that refused to split, so I led them off in the hills and FD, circled back and pulled a single from deeper in. (led the single out and FD again to make sure he was alone.) Sure enough, on the way to my party the other double came back and joined in. As soon as I noticed this, I took all 3 back to the field, gettin beat in the process, and finally succeeded in a FD, only to find the cleric running up to cast GHealing on me, and the shaman drawing aggro on the triple pull. <br>
This being LOIO, it degenerated into a finger pointing session with me being removed from the party for training them.<br>
My mistake? Or people just not used to playin with a monk?<br>
I'm still learning, just curious. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usebakiswarweaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sebakis Warweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(7/4/02 9:29:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1669.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Where, oh where did I go wrong?</span><hr size=1> Your mistake is going to LOIO.  <br>
<br>
There is lots of unexperienced people in LOIO, and the exp there completely SUCKS.  Don't worry, it wasn't your fault.  When a Monk pulls and FDs, the others should already be back.  It would only be your fault if you ran right up to the Shammy and FD'ed.  <br>
<br>
Oh by the way, make sure you turn Auto-Attack off before you press FD.   <p><center><img src=http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/Sebakis/fullsize/sebby.jpg><img src=http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/Sebakis/fullsize/sebby2.jpg></center><BR><center><font=verdana>Mustaine For Ever</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukelwan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kelwan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 95<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(7/4/02 10:17:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1669.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Where, oh where did I go wrong?</span><hr size=1> You don't tell us where in the Fort you were camping, but I have noticed some weird pathings at the front entrance. When pulling to the ledge, I have had adds there that I could not explain in any way. Almost as if they warped.<br>
<br>
Even if had been some mistake you made, removing a groupmember for a mistake when in the 20s is plain stupid. We learn from our mistakes, and it's better to do them at the lower levels. <p><font face="Gill Sans MT"><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=70469 target=_blank><font size=3 color="3300ff">Jondalar Fairfist</font></A><br>
<font size=2 color="ffdd00">Random Acts on Morell-Thule</font><br><br>
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=145989 target=_blank><font size=3 color="3300ff">Izzit</font></A><br>
<font size=2 color="ffdd00">High Eastern Erudites on Antonius Bayle</font></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usasasaz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sasasaz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(7/5/02 9:31:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1669.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Where, oh where did I go wrong?</span><hr size=1> When on my monk, if I get in trouble when pulling I tell the group to stay where they are, no casting heal or anything.<br>
Unfortunatly not to many listen, be that as it may, they usually wind up dead and me FD somewhere.<br>
<br>
As for the pathing, if your on the R Plat, heres a hint. <br>
Stay off the walls, it draws aggro.  <p><img src="http://cbrwolf.homestead.com/files/sig1.jpg">
<br>
